genresAdvancedInfo.name: renaissance
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This genre refers to the music of the Renaissance era, which spanned from the 14th to the 17th century. It is characterized by its use of polyphony, vocal harmony, and intricate melodies. Renaissance music is often performed on period instruments such as lutes, viols, and recorders.
